      "q": "How much federal contract money goes to Oregon?",
      "a": "Oregon received $1.2B in federal contract obligations in FY2026 to date. This total reflects partial fiscal-year figures and comes with a year-over-year decline of down 40.7%. Historical full-year obligations include $2.5B in FY23 and $2.4B in FY24."
    },
    {
      "q": "Which agencies award the most contracts in Oregon?",
      "a": "The Department of Defense, Department of Agriculture, and Department of Transportation award the most contracts in Oregon. The Department of Defense accounted for $622M, the Department of Agriculture $154M, and the Department of Transportation $129M in FY2026 to date."
